== Failure for non-integer powers, and generalization ==
De Moivre&#x27;s formula does not hold for non-integer powers. The derivation of de Moivre&#x27;s formula above involves a complex number raised to the integer power . If a complex number is raised to a non-integer power, the result is multiple-valued (see failure of power and logarithm identities).

